The gym is very well-maintained, with machines and other equipment all in excellent condition. Albeit on the smaller side, the layout makes excellent use of the space, and offers a solid mix of machines and training options that would satisfy most workout routines.

What I like most is the welcoming, non-intimidating atmosphere. Whether you‚Äôre new to the gym or experienced, you‚Äôll feel comfortable here. Crowd is also pretty well spaced out in the afternoons, basically little to no waiting time for equipment.

author: MM Home
text:
Review: Le Quest Anytime Fitness

Equipment: The gym has all the essentials I need. Equipment is well-maintained and ‚ÄúNEW‚Äù, so I never have to worry about something not working when I need it. And there is a new equipment coming on 9-Sept. Looking forward to it!

Cleanliness: I really appreciate how clean the gym is being maintained. The staff does a fantastic job keeping everything sanitized, and I always see other members wiping down machines after use. It gives me peace of mind knowing the environment is safe and hygienic.

Environment: The atmosphere here is welcoming and comfortable. Whether I‚Äôm in the mood for a solo workout or need some advice, the owners, YC and YS is always friendly and available to help. The other members are also respectful, which makes working out here a positive experience every time.

All in all, Le Quest AF provides exactly what I‚Äôm looking for in a gym: convenience, cleanliness, and a friendly environment. If you‚Äôre like me and value 24/7 access along with the basics for a great workout, I‚Äôd highly recommend Le Quest AF.

author: W
text:
If there is A minus 5 stars option, I would have gladly given it. On 26 June 2025 8pm, I was doing my walks around the estate and stumbled on this gym outlet. Door was opened and I was curious if I should join as a member - always been a Fitness First loyal.

Met Ding Wei the centre operator , not sure of his role there but it's completely appalling the way he treats potential customers. Here's why:

1. He told me I got to pay $65 for a penalty for entering the narrow joint without a key (door was opened by the way).

2. Proceeded to tell me I dirtied his floor by walking into the gym (now that's new and I was not treading mud in or whatever). I examined his accusations and in front of all the customers he wanted to start this ruckus so I offered sarcastically to mop his whole floor for him. Ridiculous I know.

3. I then use the centre's sanitiser spray as I had touched the steel bars and Ding Wei (wearing his All saints t shirt - funny to me because it's a funeral parlour famous in Singapore), announced loudly in front of all the gym clients, that I cannot use the sanitiser as it is company's property. I felt like he really is the worst person to be put as a front line face of the brand. I had always good impressions of anytime fitness until Ding Wei (Le Qu'est).

It's a bewildering experience and this is a neutral report. If he is the boss or actual franchisee, in a word it is boondoggle and a sacrilege. Ok more than a word. I could think of more but you catch my drift.

Kindly if the management is reading this, put someone more emotionally intelligent (at least 1000x more) to deal with potential sign ups and customers. As a business person myself, I would have rotated him to other roles (backend) instead of being the supposed charmer who gets in the sales and hitting targets, as any business owner wants.
